# Dart Coding Standards for Luvimestra

## General Guidelines
- Use camelCase for variable and function names
- Use PascalCase for class names
- Use snake_case for file names
- Add appropriate comments for complex logic
- Keep functions small and focused on a single responsibility

## State Management
- Use `setState` for state management
- Avoid complex state management libraries
- Keep state management simple and localized to widgets when possible

## Models
- Define clear model classes with final fields
- Use named parameters with required annotation
- Implement toString() for debugging purposes
- Keep models simple without complex inheritance

## UI Components
- Create reusable widgets for common UI elements
- Follow the design mockup in index.html
- Maintain consistent styling across the app
- Use the color scheme defined in the design guidelines

## Network Requests
- Handle loading states and errors gracefully
- Use try-catch blocks for error handling
- Show appropriate feedback to users during network operations

## Prohibited Practices
- No use of `freezed` package
- No `part` syntax
- No external fonts
- No local image assets (use network images)
- No `cached_network_image` package